# Purpose-driven components (KOREA 360)

Keep UI **section-based and reusable**. When building marketing pages, **create components first** (with a single, clear purpose), then compose them in pages.

- **One purpose per component**: Hero, Highlights, Gallery, CTA, Footer, etc.
- **Presentational only**: no business logic, no data fetching inside UI components.
- **Data lives in config**: put copy + assets in a dedicated data module (e.g. `src/content/...`) and pass props down.
- **Consistent layout**:
  - Container: `mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 md:px-8`
  - Section spacing: `py-16 md:py-24` (or `py-24` for hero)
  - Typography: follow project rules (large H1/H2, muted body)
- **shadcn/ui primitives**: prefer `Button`, `Card`, etc. Extend via `className`, no inline styles.

## Example pattern

✅ Good:
- `src/content/zones.ts` (data)
- `src/components/marketing/zones/ZoneHero.tsx` (purpose: zone hero)
- `src/components/marketing/zones/ZoneGallery.tsx` (purpose: image grid)
- `src/app/zones/[slug]/page.tsx` (composition)

❌ Avoid:
- hardcoding long copy/assets directly in `page.tsx`
- combining multiple sections into one large component without clear boundaries

